>B Arch<\/b>\u00a0is an art of science of designing and planning the structure in the field of construction. This course enriches the ability to create a new design according to the latest trends and technology in construction fields.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-33d45ca8 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"33d45ca8\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-10ad6c8f\" data-id=\"10ad6c8f\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3150ac7f elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"3150ac7f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width=\"498\" height=\"198\" src=\"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/03\/logo.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-165021b2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"165021b2\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h4 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">B-Architecture\u200b<\/h4>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2c025a01 elementor-widget elementor-widget-spacer\" data-id=\"2c025a01\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"spacer.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer-inner\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-50de2eda elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"50de2eda\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>B.Arch (Bachelor of Architecture) is an undergraduate degree in the field of architecture. This five-year\u00a0full-time programme is a blend of theorical and practical knowledge\u00a0for students to learn the art of planning, designing and constructing physical structures of various kinds. From ideating to mapping and overseeing the construction,\u00a0a qualified architect\u00a0is\u00a0involved at every stage of any construction project.\u00a0<\/p><p>To become an architect, interested candidates need to have a rational and artistic bent of mind along with problem-solving abilities. The career scope of B.Arch graduates in India is tremendous with the flourshing construction sector. A qualified B.Arch graduate has the option to choose their line of work from a range of areas ranging from consultants to architectural designers.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-a78f918 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"a78f918\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-513b2e1\" data-id=\"513b2e1\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2cb837b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"2cb837b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 id=\"about\">Bachelor of Architecture (B.Arch) Eligibility Criteria<\/h2><p>\u00a0<\/p><p dir=\"ltr\">Candidates who wish to pursue this 5-year bachelor of architecture programme must be aware of the eligibility criteria given below &#8211;\u00a0<\/p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Candidates who have completed their class XIIth studies or equivalent studies from a recognised Board are eligible to apply<\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Candidates should have cleared their Class XIIth qualifying exams with a minimum aggregate of 50% (45% for SC\/ST candidates)<\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Diploma holders in relevant discipline are also eligible to apply\u00a0<\/p><\/li><\/ul><h2 dir=\"ltr\">Bachelor of Architecture (B.Arch) Admission Process<\/h2><p dir=\"ltr\">There are some B.Arch offering institutions which accept NATA scores for the purpose of admission whereas some accept the scores of state-level B.Arch entrance exam scores like WBJEE, UPSEE etc. There are some B.Arch offering institutions which conduct their own entrance exams like HITSEEE, GITAM GAT etc. Based on the performance of the applicants and entrance exam scores, the institutes prepare a merit list and conduct a counselling process for the purpose of final seat allotment.\u00a0<\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" data-gtm-vis-recent-on-screen-6581841_146=\"31724\" data-gtm-vis-first-on-screen-6581841_146=\"31724\" data-gtm-vis-total-visible-time-6581841_146=\"100\" data-gtm-vis-has-fired-6581841_146=\"1\">There are also some top private B.Arch institutes in the country that offers direct admission in this prestigious 5-year programme. These institutions reserve a certain number of seats under the management quota scheme and B.Arch aspirants who want to apply for direct admission can get into one of these colleges through the management quota seats.\u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-2c0e2ca elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"2c0e2ca\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-ddd677b\" data-id=\"ddd677b\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a7f13aa elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"a7f13aa\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 dir=\"ltr\">Bachelor of Architecture (B.Arch) &#8211; Course Highlights<\/h2><div class=\"scrollTable\"><table><colgroup> <col \/> <col \/><\/colgroup><tbody><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Full Form<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><p dir=\"ltr\">Bachelor of Architecture<\/p><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Duration of the Programme<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><p dir=\"ltr\">05 Years<\/p><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Eligibility Criteria<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><p dir=\"ltr\">Class XIIth qualified candidates from Science stream and recognised Board with a minimum overall aggregate of 50% are eligible<\/p><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Admission Process<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><p dir=\"ltr\">Both Direct and Entrance based admissions<\/p><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Top Entrance Exams for B.Arch Admissions<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>National Aptitude Test in Architecture (NATA)<\/strong><\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>JEE Main (Paper-II)<\/strong><\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>WBJEE<\/strong><\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>JEE Advanced<\/strong><\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>AMUEEE<\/strong><\/p><\/li><\/ul><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Top Institutions<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>SRM Institute of Science and Technology, Chennai<\/strong><\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>Reva University, Bangalore<\/strong><\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>Birla Institute of Technology, Mesra<\/strong><\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>Techno India University, Kolkata<\/strong><\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>Integral University, Lucknow<\/strong><\/p><\/li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>Kalinga Institute of Industrial Technology, Bhubaneswar<\/strong><\/p><\/li><\/ul><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Average Programme Fee<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><p dir=\"ltr\">INR 4 LPA to INR 8 LPA<\/p><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Job Roles Offered<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><p dir=\"ltr\">Landscape Architect, Interior Designer, Contractor &amp; Researcher, Architectural Historian, Architectural Engineer, Art Director etc<\/p><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Average Starting Salary<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><p dir=\"ltr\">INR 2 LPA to INR 5 LPA<\/p><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Higher Study Options<\/strong><\/p><\/td><td><p dir=\"ltr\">M.Arch, MBA etc<\/p><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/div>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>B-Architecture B Arch\u00a0is an art of science of designing and planning the structure in the field of construction. This course enriches the ability to create a new design according to the latest trends and technology in construction fields. B-Architecture\u200b B.Arch (Bachelor of Architecture) is an undergraduate degree in the field of architecture. This five-year\u00a0full-time programme &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/educational-services\/b-architecture\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">B.architecture<\/span> Read More &raquo;<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":385,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/610"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=610"}],"version-history":[{"count":7,"href":"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/610\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":654,"href":"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/610\/revisions\/654"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultancyservices.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/385"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/pollyannaconsultan